# Core-UI Naming Conventions

- Use `PascalCase` for React component files and exported component names (`Button.tsx`, `ModalHeader.tsx`).
- Use `camelCase` for hooks/util files and exported functions (`useValidation.ts`, `formatDate.ts`).
- Hooks must start with `use` and be colocated with the related feature when possible.
- Barrel exports use `index.ts` only for re-exporting public APIs.
- Test files must be colocated and named `*.test.tsx` (for UI) or `*.test.ts` (for non-UI logic).
- Avoid vague names (`helpers.ts`, `utils.ts`) when the file can be feature-specific.

# Quick Examples

```ts
// Good
export function useModalState() {}
export function Button() {}
```
